=encoding utf8

=head1 NAME

tree-construction-xfails - Expected html5lib tree-construction failures.

=head1 FORMAT

This file is read by C<tree-construction.zzs> as a line-oriented
manifest. Each expected failure is a comment line:

  // xfail relative-fixture.dat#case-number#script-mode<TAB>reason

The file remains valid ZuzuScript so it can be syntax checked if needed,
but the harness uses the comment lines as data. Reasons should be short
and specific enough to decide when the entry can be removed.

=cut

let HTML_TREE_CONSTRUCTION_XFAIL_MANIFEST := true;

